<br> For Beyond "financial literacy is indispensable to conquer gender equality and combat violence. Women are often exposed to discrimination or economic abuse. The gender economic-financial gap is linked to lower financial knowledge by women compared to men, to a patriarchal mentality still widespread in Europe and the rest of the world and to practices that are accepted as normal some behaviors that, in reality, are expression of economic overwhelm." The Festival opens Tuesday 16 at 9.30 with the video message of the President of the European Parliament Roberta Metsola and with the institutional greetings of the mayor of Rome Capital, Roberto Gualtieri. To follow the relationship of Elisabetta Migliorelli, president of the association Oltre. We enter with the panel "Financial education against gender inequalities" attended by Gabriella Alemanno, Commissioner Consob, Paola Ansuini, Director of Communication Department Protection and Financial Education of the Bank of Italy, Claudia Cattani, President BNL BNP Paribas, Martina Rogato, Co-Chair Women7 (G7). Among the morning workshops, "Financial literacy: current account, savings, investments" and "Microcredit for women in the world". In the afternoon, a video message from the Minister of Culture Gennaro Sangiuliano will open the panel "Ferm the violence: from the culture of respect to the instruments of defence" in which he will intervene among others Martina Semenzato, president of the parliamentary commission of investigation on feministration, as well as on all forms of gender violence. Follow the panel "Economic Violence: silent and subtle. How to recognize it" with the undersecretary of the Economy Lucia Albano. In the same afternoon the workshop "UN Agenda 2030: gender equality goal". &nbsp;
<br> Wednesday 17 April, the Festival will kick off with the institutional greetings of Elena Grech, deputy director of the European Commission's Representation in Italy and with the interview with Maria Teresa Bellucci, deputy Minister of Labour and Social Policies, on "Occupation of Women and". "Work, family and birth" is the theme at the centre of both the interview with the ministra for the Family, Christmas and the Equal Opportunities, Eugenia Maria Roccella, and the next panel. In the afternoon the works will resume with the panels "Gender gap in Italy and in the world: race against time to fill it" - which will have the opening statement of Taghi Rahmani, husband of the Nobel Peace Prize Narges Mohammadi - and "Women and Stem among stereotypes to overcome and examples of excellence. The new professions." Last panel of the day, the role of public and private companies" while among the workshops planned are "Guide to gender equality certification" and "Financial literacy: current account, savings, investments".
Thursday, April 18, the Festival will open with the panel "Women, sport and economic emancipation" while in the next panel we will talk about "Stories of best practice: in comparison with the new generations". Third and final panel of the morning, "Geeeting, the theme is bipartisan." On this last day the video message of the Minister of Agriculture, the Sovereign Food and Forests, Francesco Lollobrigida, and the Minister for Disability will be projected. Alessandra Locatelli. In the afternoon, from 15, will be the turn of the panel "Together with Beyond: projects, proposals and perspectives" while in the different rooms the public can attend other workshops such as "The importance of choice" and "Economic Violence: if you know the Avoid". It will be present at the event the Camper of the project "This is not love" of the State Police, the permanent campaign of the State Police to counter the phenomenon of violence against women and prevent feminists.&nbsp;

